# Sample conservative Codex rules (copy into your user rules folder)

- Ask before `git push` or any remote publish action.
- Never print environment variables or secrets (e.g. `OPENAI_API_KEY`).
- Ask before any `curl`, `Invoke-WebRequest`, or other HTTP calls.
- Prefer `npm` over other package managers.
- Avoid destructive commands (`rm -rf`, `git reset --hard`) unless explicitly requested.

